\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes the framework by which the Elko County Information Operations Department (ECIO) plans for,
 prepares against,
 and recovers from disruptions to IT services.
 It defines the governing requirements for business impact analysis,
 asset criticality classification,
 recovery objective-setting,
 continuity plan maintenance,
 backup governance,
 continuity plan activation,
 and operational recovery sequencing.
 It provides the planning artifacts against which operational incident response execution under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 operates,
 and it establishes the receiving mechanics for operational recovery authority following a cybersecurity incident response phase governed by Chapter 4 policies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
